Procedure:
Step 1: Create Project Folder

Create a folder named:

LibraryManagementSystem

Open it in VS Code

Step 2: Open Terminal

Go to:

Terminal → New Terminal
Step 3: Initialize Git Repository
git init
Step 4: Create a Python File

Create a file named:

main.py

Add code:

print("Hello Library Management System")
Step 5: Add Files to Git
git add .
Step 6: Commit Files
git commit -m "Initial commit"
Step 7: Create Repository in GitHub
Go to GitHub
Click New Repository
Enter name:
library-management-system
Click Create Repository
Step 8: Connect Local Repo to GitHub
git remote add origin https://github.com/your-username/library-management-system.git
Step 9: Push Code to GitHub
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
📌 Additional Git Commands (For Lab Questions)
Check status
git status
View changes
git diff
View commit history
git log
🌿 Branch Commands (Feature Development)
Create branch
git branch login-feature
Switch branch
git checkout login-feature
Merge branch
git checkout main
git merge login-feature
🔄 Undo Changes
Discard changes
git checkout -- filename
🚫 Ignore Files

Create file:

.gitignore

Add:

*.log
*.tmp
🔄 Pull Latest Changes
git pull origin main
